tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows markedly elevated serum creatinine and proteinuria, indicating significant renal impairment. Mildly elevated ALT suggests possible hepatic involvement. Low serum protein may reflect protein loss or decreased synthesis. Urinalysis reveals glucosuria, ketonuria, and proteinuria, with abnormal urine appearance and color, but no evidence of infection. Findings are consistent with acute or chronic kidney disease, possibly with nephrotic features and metabolic derangements. Prompt nephrology evaluation is recommended.
